MINI REDIS
==========

A Redis server implemented with C++11 and Boost.

FEATURES
--------

* Fully implements the RESP2 protocol.
* Supported Redis commands(16):
	PING, SAVE, LOAD, SET, GET, DEL, EXPIRE, PEXPIRE, EXPIREAT, PEXPIREAT,
	TTL, PTTL, INCR, INCRBY, DECR, DECRBY

PERSISTENCE
-----------

* SAVE [TO <path>]
	Save a snapshot of the current database to the specified path.
	If no path is provided, `dump.mrdb' will be used.

* LOAD [FROM <path>]
	Load snapshot data from the specified path.
	If no path is provided, `dump.mrdb' will be used.

DEPENDENCIES
------------

* A C++ compiler supporting the C++11 standard.
* Boost Library installed on the system.

BUILD
-----

	$ cmake -B build
	$ cmake --build build

RUN
---

	$ ./build/server
